'''Arne Kokkvoll''' (1925 – 19 September 1998) was a [[Norwegians|Norwegian]] historian, librarian/archivist and politician for the [[Norwegian Labour Party|Labour Party]].
He was born at Kokkvollen in [[Røros]], and took the [[cand.philol.]] degree in 1957.<ref name=obit>{{cite journal|last=Bergh|first=Trond|authorlink=Trond Bergh|year=1999|title=Arne Kokkvoll (1925–1998)|journal=Arbeiderhistorie|issue=1999|pages=270–271|language=Norwegian}}</ref> His master's thesis was about [[Johannes Nesse]], and it was published later as a book.<ref name=60y>{{cite news|title=Arne Kokkvoll 60 år: Historie en viktig del av vår samtid|last=Vance|first=Bibi Plahte|date=26 October 1985|work=Aftenposten|page=10|language=Norwegian}}</ref> Kokkvoll worked as a teacher and was a [[research assistant]] at the [[Norwegian Institute of Local History]] before being hired as director of the [[Labour Movement Archive and Library]]. He held this post until 1987, and was also acting [[docent]] at the [[University of Trondheim]] from 1976 to 1978.<ref name=obit/> He was later the director of Olavsgruva Museum in Røros.<ref name=60y/>
He was also a leader of the [[Norwegian Movement for Vietnam]] from 1969 to 1972,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.klassekampen.no/51141/article/item/null|title=Vietnam samlet protestene|last=Undheim Larsen|first=Dag Eivind|date=15 February 2008|work=Klassekampen|language=Norwegian|accessdate=12 January 2009}}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|title=Arne Kokkvoll|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Arne_Kokkvoll|language=Norwegian|accessdate=1 September 2010}}</ref> and he led ''Oslo Arbeidersamfunn'' from 1966 to 1967. From 1988 to 1991 he was the mayor of Røros, representing the Labour Party.<ref name=obit/><ref name=snl/>
Kokkvoll was not a prolific writer, but held many lectures, especially for the labour movement.<ref name=obit/> He published ''Av og for det arbeidende folket'' in 1981, and he was the editor for the six-volume work ''[[Arbeiderbevegelsens historie i Norge]]'', released between 1985 and 1990.<ref name=snl/>
